+ @apolcyn @jtattermusch interop folks

@ejona86 Let's decouple of SNI from grpc interop tests. In grpc interops (c++, python, php at least). I have not checked Java/Go interop tests. Interop client will by default use foo.test.google.fr for hostname override and **always** override targetname. There is no way to not override. In other words, if you don't want override, you have to manually set ssl_target_name_overrides to be the same as the server_host. If it is something we don't like, let @apolcyn and @jtattermusch fix the interop tests.

In the case of non-interop-testing, users are not required to set grpc.ssl_target_name_override. It won't be set by default. If grpc.ssl_target_name_override is set, then SNI will be kicked in. Otherwise, there won't be SNI.
